                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Long context modeling is a fundamental challenge for Transformer- based (Vaswani et al., 2017) LLMs due to their inherent self- attention mechanism. Much previous research (Child et al., 2019; Beltagy et al., 2020; Rae et al., 2019; Choromanski et al., 2020; Bulatov et al., 2022; Zheng et al., 2022; Wu et al., 2022; Bulatov et al., 2023; Ding et al., 2023) attempts to tackle the long context issue through architectural innovations of an LLM. While they approach long context with a significant reduction in computation and memory complexity, they often struggle to overcome the notable decline"
